### 8.3 Deal Structuring Recommendations

#### 8.3.1 Price Adjustment Mechanism

**Recommendation:** Negotiate a $25M–$35M escrow tied to the following milestone releases:

| Milestone | Escrow Release | Timeline |
|-----------|---------------|----------|
| Rust rewrite production deployment (≥90% feature parity) | 40% of escrow | 12 months post-close |
| Rust performance benchmarks met (defined thresholds) | 25% of escrow | 15 months post-close |
| CTO retention (active employment) | 20% of escrow | 18 months post-close |
| No material customer attrition (top 5 accounts retained) | 15% of escrow | 12 months post-close |

#### 8.3.2 IP Indemnification

Require DataFlow Systems to provide representations and warranties that:
- All 14 patents are fully assigned to the company with no prior employer claims
- No patents were developed using resources of any third party
- No pending or threatened IP litigation exists

Supplement with Representations and Warranties Insurance (RWI) covering IP claims up to $75M.

#### 8.3.3 Retention Pool Enhancement

Increase the engineering retention pool from $15M to $22M–$25M. Restructure the cliff from 18 months to a tiered schedule (25% at 6 months, 50% at 12 months, 100% at 18 months) to reduce the departure incentive at the cliff boundary. Establish a separate CTO-specific retention agreement of $3M–$5M tied to technical milestones rather than time alone.

#### 8.3.4 Price Range Guidance

Based on current findings, the due diligence team recommends the following pricing posture:

| Scenario | Recommended Approach |
|----------|---------------------|
| Prompt injection determined to be isolated/negligible, production systems materially clean, CTO retention secured | Proceed at $320M with $25M escrow structure |
| Prompt injection investigation inconclusive, production systems show additional quality gaps, CTO retention uncertain | Reduce offer to $285M–$300M with $35M escrow |
| Prompt injection determined adversarial, systemic engineering quality issues confirmed, CTO departure likely | Recommend transaction suspension pending further investigation |

